remarks.para:
Assuming we have the library configurator object:

...
ILibraryConfigurator configurator = LibraryConfigurator.Current;
...
Configurator.ConfigureWindowsService(name, "Description", new SampleServiceBehaviour());
...

or

Configurator.ConfigureWindowsService(name, "Description", "SampleServiceBehaviourName");

example.code:
public class MyBatchHandler : BatchHandler
{

    public override void DoWork(string name, CancellationToken cancellation)
    {
        // Do something. Always respect the cancellation token
    }

}

remarks.para:
Assuming we have the library configurator object given or created:

...
ILibraryConfigurator configurator = LibraryConfigurator.Current;
...
Configurator.ConfigureWindowsService(name, "Description", new SampleServiceBehaviour());
...

or

Configurator.ConfigureWindowsService(name, "Description", "SampleServiceBehaviourName");

remarks.code:

ILibraryConfigurator configurator = LibraryConfigurator.Current;
...
Configurator.ConfigureBatchWindowsService("name", "description", batches => batches
   .AddBatch("batch running every 10 seconds", handler1, new IntervalTimeScheduler(new TimeSpan(0, 0, 10)))
   .AddBatch("batch running every November 11th at 11:11am", handler2, new CronTimeScheduler("0 11 11 11 11 ?")))
);
...

